race.description: Gordon Pub Punters, A Gpg Hotel Maiden Handicap
race.comment: Very tricky. WESTERN LANE (2) races forward and didn't quite put it all together last preparation. Two back went close at Kembla Grange, rating well, and he's prepared for his return with a 4.3L trial win at Rosehill. Will use the low barrier and a bold run is on the cards. TURF LUCK (1) improved sharply at his second start when beaten less than 1L here over 1200m. Jay Ford stays aboard and the blinkers go on for the first time. Will have taken further fitness and learning and maps well. THE WAY AHEAD (5) went close over 1000m at Wyong before the spell and led there first-up and the fitness gave out late. Will be sharper today and the shorter sprint should advantage. Can make the finish. Stablemate CRESTWOOD (7) deserves plenty of consideration on debut. Has a wide gate but looked good winning at Warwick Farm in the latest of three trials.
